CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 27, 1946, pg. 17 reads: "Newlyweds Feted - Mr. and Mrs. Charles Mason, newlyweds of Columbus, Ohio, recently visited the Smoky City as guests of the groom's sister, Mrs. Helen Williams of 2467 Chauncey Drive. The trio posed for this shot in front of Mrs. Williams' home, and the bride, formerly Miss Darling Bryant, is on the left. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of newlyweds Darling Bryant Mason and Charles Mason, standing with sister Helen Williams on lawn at her home at 2467 Chauncey Drive
